Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 15.38 percent / 0.00 percent / 0.00 percent / 7.69 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: following epidemiological investigations carried out in the State of Minas Gerais, another outbreak was detected. An outbreak was reported in the State of Sao Paulo, apparently without any epidemiological link with the others. The farm where the animals are is a stud farm with animals used for sport. The date of last occurrence of glanders in the State of Sao Paulo is 2008. Epidemiological investigations are on-going.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Agricultural Laboratory, LANAGRO-PE (national laboratory) / Equidae / complement fixation test (CFT) / 18 Jul 2012 / Positive
Veterinarian of the Official Veterinary Services (national laboratory) / Equidae / mallein test / 10 Apr 2013 / Positive
Laboratory Equalli (private laboratory) / Equidae / complement fixation test / CFT) / 13 Mar 2013 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

